title: Sketchbook Folio, "Diana and Callisto", 1810–20
medium: Pen and brown ink, brush and brown wash, over black chalk on white laid paper
inscribed: in pen and brown ink at lower left margin: 38; at center right: Anibale Caracci Parigi. On verso: Coregio Modena
creditline: Museum purchase through gift of various donors
description: Diana sits on rock at center pointing right, across body of Callisto. Four bathing nymphs at lower left, and two others in background shadows.
